{
  "stem": "214.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't, maybe he drank a little, maybe he played cards a little.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I really don't know-- Shia was his name.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he was very-- unfortunately, he got-- he was also killed in one of those--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he went to Warsaw-- so anyway, the Jews had to leave Skierniewice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had the-- they could go to Warsaw-- actually, everybody was supposed to go to Warsaw, which was about 60 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No transportation was being provided.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It really became quite a panicky situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my cousin, Shia, he was-- [NON-ENGLISH] was the name of this Pole.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember he's also the one who gave us those little, you know, birth certificates which were totally false.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it started that-- and this was my mother's, there were war conferences, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were those rumors that Skierniewice is going to become Junderein, because all those places are on the west side of the Vistula.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Vistula divides north and south Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were rumors that on the east side of the Vistula, maybe there are not ghettos yet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And since my sister and I began-- started knocking ourselves around, you know, some people from [NON-ENGLISH], which was very close, to Miedzyrec-- came to Miedzyrzec.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, traveling by train was absolutely punishable-- everything was punishable by death.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, we really were supposed to wear already those-- no, this was- yes, we we're supposed to wear those white bands, the arm bands.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you took off the arm band and you just took your-- but I don't know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't even think that you had any feeling of-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I suppose when you are young, you are-- it was not any bravery.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was-- I don't know, but we did it several times.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
